title: Volleyball Roundup: Clear Fork wins
text:
Volleyball Roundup: Clear Fork wins Staff report 10:54 p.m. EDT October 20, 2015 STK Stock 
Division II Sectional 
Clear Fork 3 Oak Harbor 2 
The Lady Colts (16-7) defeated Oak Harbor in five set (25-23, 25-23, 11-25, 21-25, 17-15) to advance to the Sectional final on Thursday. Michaela Barnett had 12 kills, Amelia Moore had 11 kills, 18 digs and had 11 assists and Tabi Hamilton had 18 assists and three aces. 
Vermilion 3, Shelby 0 
Shelby lost in three sets (23-25, 22-25, 15-25) to Vermilion on Tuesday in Sectional semi-final action. Maddie Fidler had nine kills, Madison Alfrey had three aces and 14 digs, Kennadie Goth had three aces, Chelsea Barnd had one block and Kadie Hoffman had 12 assists. 
Norwalk 3, Ontario 0 
Ontario lost in three sets (8-25, 13-25, 7-25) to Norwalk in Sectional action on Tuesday. 
Division III Sectional 
Highland 3, Mount Gilead 0 
Highland (21-2) defeated Mount Gilead in three sets (25-9, 25-13, 25-12) in Division III Sectional semi-final action on Tuesday. Borgin Dennman had 13 kills and five aces, Taylor Belcher had 11 aces and 10 assists, Jorden Goodmand had 15 assists, Marlese Ferguson had 11 assists and Bridget Oder had 15 digs. 
Fairbanks 3, Northmor 1 
Northmor (12-10) lost to Fairbanks in four sets (17-25, 25-23, 18-25, 21-25) in Division III Sectional semi-final action on Tuesday. Jordan Zoll had 23 assists and two aces, Anna Donner had 14 kills, Kelsie Fike had two aces, Karlee Carroll had 15 digs while Mikayla Briggs and Hope Miracle each had one block. 
Utica 3, Cardington 1 
Cardington lost to Utica in four sets (20-25, 26-24, 25-14, 25-7) in Sectional semi-final action on Tuesday. 
Orrville 3, Loudonville 0 
The Redbirds lost in three sets (7-25, 11-25, 4-25) to Orrville on Tuesday. Emma Hinkle led Loudonville in setting with six assist and two points. Katie Kline also had two points and a team high 10 digs. Shayla Edmondson and Kaitlyn Adams each had two kills. 
Division IV Sectional 
South Central 3, Danbury 0 
South Central (13-10) defeated Danbury in three sets (25-11, 25-7, 25-10) in Sectional action on Tuesday. Lexi Adams had 10 kills wsihll Olivia Keysor had eight kills, two aces and five digs. Erin Broan had five aces, Sarah Oney had six digs and Maddie Albert had 32 assists for the Trojans. 
Crestline 3, St. Peterâ€™s 0 
The Bulldogs defeats the Spartans in three sets on Tuesday in the Division IV Sectional semi-final. 
Mansfield Christian 3, New London 1 
The Flames defeated New London in four sets (14-25, 28-26, 25-20, 25-23) in Sectional play on Tuesday night. Ashton Trueblood and Miranda Young each had two aces, Abi Steensland had 12 kills while Kilee Stoner had six kills and four blocks. Lauren Banks had 27 assists and Trueblood added 17 digs. 
Sandusky St. Mary Central Catholic 3, Lucas 2 
The Cubs lost to St. Mary Central Catholic in five sets (27-25, 25-15, 11-25, 20-25, 12-15) on Tuesday in Sectional play. 
Norwalk St. Paul 3, Plymouth 0 
Plymouth lost to St. Paul in three sets (3-25, 6-25, 3-25) in Sectional semi-final action on Tuesday. 
OCSAA NW Region Tournament 
Christian Academy 3, Temple Christian 1 
Temple Christian lost in four sets to Christian Academy (25-22, 19-25, 20-25, 9-25) on Monday in the Ohio Christian Schools Athletic Association Tournament. Michelle McLurea had nine kills, Haley Costick had six kills, Brooklyn Hannan had seven aces and Robyn Hewitt had three aces. Read or Share this story: http://ohne.ws/1RV11TQ MORE STORIES
